The Imo Police Command says it has launched surveillance to arrest suspected killers of Mr Ifeanyi Ozoemena, Chairman, All Progressives Congress (APC), Logara/Umuohiagu Ward in Ngor-Okpala LGA. The Commissioner of Police in Imo, Mr Dasuki Galandachi, gave the assurance in Owerri on Thursday in an interview with the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN). Ozoemena was murdered by suspected gunmen on Tuesday night after presiding over a party meeting in the ward in preparation for the postponed elections. The situation threw APC members in the council area into mourning. The commissioner of police has, however, called for calm. Galandachi said that the suspects would soon be arrested, adding that security forces had been deployed to restore peace in the area. “I assure the family members of Ozoemena, APC members and the general public that the suspected killers of the APC chieftain will be tracked down soon,’’ he said. (NAN) Members of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in Logara/Umuohiagu Ward of Ngor Okpala Local Government Area of Imo State have been thrown into mourning following the murder of their ward chairman, Mr. Ifeanyi Ozoemena. Ozoemena was shot dead on Tuesday night by some assailants.   The slain party chairman, who… In "Metro and Crime" Members of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in Logara/Umuohiagu Ward of Ngor Okpala LGA, Imo State have been thrown into mourning following the gruesome murder of their ward chairman, Mr Ifeanyi Ozoemena who was shot dead Tuesday night by unknown gunmen. The slain party chairman who hails from Umuokeada Logara,… In "News" APC Congress   The All Progressives Congress (APC) Local Government Area congress on Saturday suffered setback as protesters from various LGAs invaded the State Government House condemning the affirmation of candidates, vowing that if nothing was done, there will be mass exodus from the party. Findings by the Sunday Telegraph… In "News"